# 🎓 GTECH University Campus Network

![Cisco](https://img.shields.io/badge/Tool-Cisco%20Packet%20Tracer-blue)
![Network](https://img.shields.io/badge/Type-Campus%20Network-green)
![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/Status-Completed-brightgreen)

---

## 📌 Project Overview
This project is a **multi-building campus network** designed and implemented using Cisco Packet Tracer.

It connects four main buildings within GTECH University:
- 🏢 Business Block  
- 🏢 Administration Block  
- 🏢 Technology Block  
- 🏢 Health Block  

The network is designed to be **scalable, secure, and efficient**, supporting communication across departments and internet connectivity.

---

## 🎯 Objectives
- Design a hierarchical network (Core, Distribution, Access)
- Implement VLAN-based segmentation
- Enable inter-VLAN communication using SVIs
- Configure dynamic routing using OSPF
- Provide automatic IP addressing (DHCP)
- Implement NAT (PAT + Static NAT)
- Perform real-world troubleshooting

---

## ⚙️ Technologies Used
- VLANs  
- Inter-VLAN Routing (SVIs)  
- OSPF Routing Protocol  
- DHCP  
- NAT (PAT & Static NAT)  
- Cisco Packet Tracer  

---

## 🏗 Network Design
- Multi-layer architecture (Access → Distribution → Core)
- Multiple routers and multilayer switches
- Department-based VLAN segmentation
- Server deployment in each building
- Full inter-building connectivity

---

## 🧪 Testing & Verification
✔️ VLAN communication verified  
✔️ Inter-VLAN routing successful  
✔️ OSPF routing operational  
✔️ DHCP allocation working  
✔️ NAT translation tested  
✔️ End-to-end connectivity achieved  

---

## 🛠 Troubleshooting Highlights
- Fixed VLAN misconfigurations (Layer 2 issues)  
- Corrected SVI IP addressing (Layer 3 issues)  
- Resolved DHCP pool errors  
- Fixed incorrect default gateways  
- Identified and corrected routing issues  

